main event: A citizen in Champaign, Illinois observed an unidentified flying object in the sky northwest of Champaign on September 24, 1960.
interesting points: The object was oval in shape, four times the size of the full moon, and yellow-white in color.
The object appeared to wobble or vibrate as it traveled, and moved very fast, changing direction during flight.
The object was observed for approximately 10 minutes, first at around 9:00 PM and last at around 9:50 PM.
The observers were watching the stars when they first sighted the object, which stopped, appeared to grow smaller, and faded from view.

The investigating officer noted that the description of the object resembled familiar UFO sightings, with an artificial shell and bright lights, giving the impression of a high-speed controlled flight.
sighted object: an oval-shaped, yellow-white object in the sky
